        <groupName xml:id="BTS">BTS (방탄소년단)</groupName>
        <bgInfo>
            <p>BTS is a 7-member group under the company <compMent labelRef="BigHitEnt">Big Hit Entertainment</compMent>. Over the course of their 7-years career, the group has managed to become the world’s biggest K-Pop group. They continue to break records and make millions of dollars (billions in the Korean currency, won) of profit from concerts, merchandising, and album sales. </p>
            
            <p>A fact that’s not as well-known about BTS is the level of creative control they’re often given over their own music. While they aren't entirely self-producing like groups <groupMent artistRef="Seventeen">Seventeen</groupMent> or <groupMent artistRef="Stray-Kids">Stray Kids</groupMent>, members <memberMent artistRef="RM">RM</memberMent> and <memberMent artistRef="Suga">Suga</memberMent> do an impressive amount of the producing, composing, and lyrical writing throughout the group’s discography. <memberMent artistRef="RM">RM</memberMent>, BTS’s leader, has the 4th highest number of copyrighted songs in all of K-Pop, with main rapper <memberMent artistRef="Suga">Suga</memberMent> at a respectable 9th place, as seen in <link linkURL="https://www.allkpop.com/article/2020/10/kpop-idols-who-own-the-most-copyrights-updated-in-october-2020">this Allkpop article</link>.</p>
        </bgInfo>
